QTWriteEvent(Impinj.QTWriteAccessParams, AccessFilter, AntennaInfo) - Method in class com.mot.rfid.api3.Impinj
This method is used to write QT Control data on all the QT tags that match the AccessFilter criteria if specified.It can enable/disable public-private memory map and short range modes of QT tags.
QTWriteWait(String, Impinj.QTWriteAccessParams, AntennaInfo) - Method in class com.mot.rfid.api3.Impinj
Performs QTWrite operation on an Impinj QT tag.It can enable/disable public memory map and Short range modes of a QT tag.However,short range mode is currently not supported.Besides,persist flag applies the above settings to either volatile/non-volatile memories.
